<br>
It appears to not be readable on their site..they want to sell issues, after all..   <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Couple of quotes from the article:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
&quot;There's been one proposal practically every year for a new space launch system like the shuttle since the shuttle first flew,&quot; says Bob Parkinson, who managed the now defunct Hotol reusable launch vehicle project for British Aerospace in the 1980's.  &quot;And all of them have been better than we have now.&quot;<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
&quot;Rarely do you see an instance where state-of-the-art technology enters service,&quot; says Keith Cowing, editor of Nasawatch.com.  &quot;You live with whatever moment in time you froze your design.&quot;<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I personally like <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.andrews-space.com/en/index.html">Andrew's Space &amp; Technology's</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> Mach 6 Gryphon (pictured on this issue of PS's cover) but, of course, have not been able to find a whole lot of info on it, yet..save for a bit from this article and and some info about It's propulsion system;  <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.andrews-space.com/en/corporate/Alchemist.html">Alchemist.</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
The vehicle shown on our cover, Andrew's Space &amp; Technology's Gryphon concept, is farther reaching.  A plane-like launcher accellerates an orbiter to Mach 6 before a high-altitude release.  Gryphon's innovative propulsions system uses liquid oxygen, drawn and compressed from the air, as fuel.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
..and, lastly, this from <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.hobbyspace.com">HobbySpace.com</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
NASA Awards US$767 Million in Space Launch Initiative Contracts + Options - Andrews S&amp;T - May.21.01 <br>
<br>
Andrews will use the money to build a prototype of its Alchemist processing system. In the Andrews two stage Gryphon, the Alchemist gathers oxygen from the air and liquefies it while the vehicle flies at low altitudes for a hour or so until there is sufficient amount for use with a rocket to fly to a high altitude where an orbital stage is released.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.whitetoweronline.com"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.whitetoweronline.com/hall/icons/barth-sig.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=markix@nuclearspace>MarkIX</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Space Hotel Magnate</span><br>  Posts: 210<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(4/14/03 5:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=870.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Beyond the STS..</span><hr size=1> Just like the inflight refueling concept only more expensive and using untried technological configuration of course NASA would love it now that They (you know Them) have their hooks into it it will go nowhere or be expensive <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hamster@nuclearspace>Hamster</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>spacefaring rodent</span><br>  Posts: 1251<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(4/14/03 8:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=870.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://image1ex.villagephotos.com/extern/935754.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Beyond the STS..</span><hr size=1> Once NASA gets its hands on something like that it's pretty much a given we can kiss it goodbye.  I've lost all hope that NASA will bui